attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2, for GNU/Linux 2.6.18, BuildID[sha1]=539b591b1fae946ffa31ee02639b4bbf65e30308, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This ELF binary is a multi-threaded backdoor/RAT (Remote Access Trojan). It establishes persistence by daemonizing itself and copying itself to a new location under `/tmp/` before executing the copy. It communicates over the network using a custom protocol with custom encryption (key: "r0st@#$"). Core malicious capabilities include providing a remote interactive shell via `/bin/sh` (using `openpty`), extensive file management (upload, download, delete, rename, list directories), and gathering system information (OS version, network interfaces).
